---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | ToolGrid" description="Learn how ToolGrid protects your privacy with our zero-trust architecture.">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl py-20">
    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="text-muted-foreground"><strong>Last Updated: June 2026</strong></p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Zero-Trust Architecture</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">ToolGrid is built on a fundamental principle of absolute privacy. Because our tools run entirely client-side using WebAssembly (WASM) within your browser, <strong>we do not upload, process, or store your files on our servers.</strong></p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. Data Collection</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">We do not require accounts, and we do not collect personal identifying information. We may use basic, anonymized analytics to understand general website traffic and tool usage patterns, strictly without tracking individual users.</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">We use Cloudflare for hosting and CDN services. Cloudflare may log standard network request data for security and performance purposes.</p>
    
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
